    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect MBSFN subframe configuration parsing in UE PHY\n\n### Summary\nThe UE PHY layer contained a critical bug in parsing MBSFN subframe configurations received from eNB in SIB2. When processing MBSFN configurations with `fourFrames` allocation pattern, the code incorrectly accessed the `oneFrame` buffer field instead of the `fourFrames` field, leading to corrupted subframe pattern interpretation.\n\nThis bug caused incorrect MBSFN subframe identification, resulting in missed MBSFN data receptions and signaling procedure failures that violated 3GPP message flow requirements.\n\nThe issue was present in both `phy_config_sib2_ue` and `phy_config_mbsfn_list_ue` functions where the field access was hardcoded to `choice.oneFrame` even in the `fourFrames` processing branch.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/lte_init_ue.c`: Corrected field access in both MBSFN configuration functions\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/phy_init.h`: Fixed function documentation inconsistency\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder network conditions with MBSFN configured using `fourFrames` allocation pattern, UE would fail to correctly identify MBSFN subframes, leading to:\n- Missing MBSFN data receptions\n- Incorrect RRC signaling procedure sequences\n- Potential RRC connection release due to MBSFN synchronization failures\n\nThe issue was reproducible by configuring an eNB with MBSFN subframe configuration using `fourFrames` pattern and observing UE behavior during MBSFN data reception.\n"
}